Sec. 111.004. BALING. (a) Each bale of cotton ginned by a
ginner shall be wrapped so that:
(1) the bale will be completely covered when compressed and
the ends of the bale are closed and well sewn; and
(2) the markings on the bale will remain intact and visible
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 700 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

under ordinary conditions.
(b) In compressing, recompressing, baling, or rebaling cotton,
each person owning, operating, or working for a compress in this
state shall, prior to delivery of a bale to a common carrier, bind
and tie the bale so that the bale is free of:
(1) dangerously exposed ends of bands or buckles; or
(2) dangerously exposed or protruding parts of ties, bands,
buckles, or splices.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1299, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

